        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 4. Penis of Achaiohydrobia moreana. Scale bar: 200 μm." , "Figure 2. Shells of Achaiohydrobia moreana A holotype; shell measurements are shown: a = shell height, b = body whorl breadth, c = aperture height, d = spire height, e = aperture breadth, α = apex angle, β = angle between body whorl suture and horizontal surface. Scale bar: 1 mm." , "Figure 6. Protoconchs of Achaiohydrobia moreana. Scale bar: 200 μm." , "Figure 7. Radulae of Achaiohydrobia moreana. Scale bar: 25 μm." , "Figure 3. Renal and pallial section of female reproductive organs of Achaiohydrobia moreana; drawing not to the scale (bc - bursa copulatrix, cbc - duct of the bursa, ov - oviduct, ovs - spiral of renal oviduct, rs - receptaculum seminis). Scale bar: 200 μm." ;
